WEBVTT

00:06.924 --> 00:09.962
Gentlemen,
we are about to embark.

00:12.304 --> 00:13.420
Come on!

00:13.555 --> 00:16.093
I wanted to say something
all profound for posterity.

00:16.225 --> 00:17.636
Save it, "Hobbit" Oppenheimer.

00:17.768 --> 00:19.805
We don't even know
if it worked this time.

00:19.937 --> 00:20.895
Well?

00:20.896 --> 00:22.558
Seems like a apple.

00:22.689 --> 00:23.689
Take a bite.

00:23.774 --> 00:24.810
Uh, y-you.

00:24.942 --> 00:26.308
I'm gonna run diagnostics,

00:26.443 --> 00:28.560
make sure the genetic sequence
isn't compromised.

00:28.695 --> 00:30.106
Yeah, make sure
there aren't any,

00:30.239 --> 00:31.571
you know,
fly parts it in.

00:31.698 --> 00:34.486
Seriously, double
and triple fly-check.

00:34.618 --> 00:36.280
Diagnostics look clean.

00:39.706 --> 00:41.663
- Hmm.
- Well?

00:41.792 --> 00:44.830
It tastes like success!

00:44.962 --> 00:45.962
Yes!

00:46.046 --> 00:49.039
So who's gonna volunteer
to be our first human subject?

00:49.174 --> 00:51.632
Whoa, what? Yeah, look, no way.
You're crazy.

00:51.760 --> 00:53.440
We're nowhere near ready
for human testing.

00:53.470 --> 00:55.928
White, go find Hank.
He'd do it for the free apple.

00:56.056 --> 00:57.342
Doc, no!

00:57.474 --> 01:00.262
This is literally the first
apple we haven't massacred.

01:00.394 --> 01:02.727
We need to study it,
repeat the experiment,

01:02.854 --> 01:05.312
analyze and reanalyze
all the data

01:05.440 --> 01:09.059
and then, <i>maybe</i>, in a couple
of months, move up to mice.

01:09.194 --> 01:10.230
Ahoy, chairmen!

01:10.362 --> 01:11.648
If'n you're done fiddling

01:11.780 --> 01:13.988
with your fancy
food processor,

01:14.116 --> 01:16.358
we need your signature
on these here...

01:16.493 --> 01:18.325
Aah!

01:18.453 --> 01:21.036
Not ready
for human testing.

01:21.164 --> 01:22.996
Congratulations, Captain!

01:23.125 --> 01:26.539
You've just made
super science history!

01:26.670 --> 01:28.957
Now, right this way, Captain.
Billy's just gonna...

01:29.089 --> 01:30.089
He's done it!

01:30.173 --> 01:33.712
Repeat, Venture has done it!
We are go for extraction.

01:41.059 --> 01:43.176
Huh?
What the...

01:43.312 --> 01:45.429
Mayday! Mayday!
I've been spotted.

01:45.564 --> 01:46.850
Initiating evasive...

01:51.445 --> 01:54.188
No! No way!
Absolutely...

01:54.323 --> 01:56.861
I am not joining
some dumb team.

01:56.992 --> 01:58.403
You're not joining a team.

01:58.535 --> 02:00.697
You're just filling in
for one job.

02:00.829 --> 02:03.116
I had to pull a lot of strings
to get you this gig.

02:03.248 --> 02:06.241
Well, unpull them, then.
Push them back! Whatever!

02:06.376 --> 02:07.662
I don't want it!

02:07.794 --> 02:09.330
No, but you need it!

02:09.463 --> 02:11.204
The Guild wants this thing
so bad,

02:11.340 --> 02:13.548
they're offering
a full EMA level upgrade

02:13.675 --> 02:14.694
if the heist is successful.

02:14.718 --> 02:17.756
A heist? Sweet!
What's the score?

02:17.888 --> 02:19.254
Classified, Gary.
I'm sorry.

02:19.389 --> 02:21.301
It doesn't matter
because I'm not inter...

02:21.433 --> 02:23.720
Don't you dare put that
empty milk carton back!

02:23.852 --> 02:25.593
There's still some left!
It's a sip.

02:25.729 --> 02:29.063
A sip? <i>A</i> sip?
Go get more milk.

02:29.191 --> 02:31.934
Look, I'm just not
a team player, okay, honey?

02:32.069 --> 02:34.561
The Monarch is
strictly a solo act!

02:34.696 --> 02:36.187
Yes, I know, sweetness.

02:36.323 --> 02:38.781
You're a precious unicorn,
beautiful and unique,

02:38.909 --> 02:41.117
but can you at least just go
and meet with them

02:41.244 --> 02:45.033
before you make up your mind,
please, for me?

02:51.004 --> 02:52.370
Hi-o, guy-o!

02:52.506 --> 02:54.668
Glad you could come
on such short notice.

02:54.800 --> 02:57.258
Sashay on in here.
The meeting's started.

02:57.386 --> 03:00.595
Well, hey, all.
Look at what the me dragged in.

03:00.722 --> 03:03.931
Team, this here's Tiny Eagle's
replacement, the Mighty Monarch.

03:04.059 --> 03:06.096
Mighty Monarch,
meet the team.

03:06.228 --> 03:09.096
Dot Com,
hackstress extraordinaire.

03:09.231 --> 03:10.147
Hey.

03:10.148 --> 03:12.435
And to her lovely left
is Tunnel Vision,

03:12.567 --> 03:13.567
our resident digger.

03:13.610 --> 03:14.610
Hey there, chief.

03:14.653 --> 03:17.191
That funny-looking fella
is called Presto Change-O.

03:17.322 --> 03:19.359
Greetings!

03:19.491 --> 03:21.778
And over here
you've got Ramburglar,

03:21.910 --> 03:23.401
top-shelf smash-and-grab man.

03:23.537 --> 03:24.328
'Sup?

03:24.329 --> 03:26.286
Lastly, there's Driver X.

03:26.415 --> 03:27.701
Ooh, he ain't much for words,

03:27.833 --> 03:31.577
but his getaway driving's
poetry in motion.

03:31.712 --> 03:32.873
Hey.

03:33.004 --> 03:35.121
So, uh, I'm a little late
to this party, and my wi...

03:35.257 --> 03:38.250
the councilwoman, uh,
was kind of hazy on the details.

03:38.385 --> 03:40.923
Uh, what exactly is the job?

03:41.054 --> 03:43.797
Oh, you're in for a treat,
june bug.

03:43.932 --> 03:47.141
We're fixing to hit that there
Venture headquarters.

03:47.269 --> 03:49.556
Listen, Doc,
I really need to talk to you

03:49.688 --> 03:51.145
about this security breach.

03:51.273 --> 03:52.559
Oh, pfft, later.

03:52.691 --> 03:54.460
I want to get right to work
on my press release.

03:54.484 --> 03:56.004
I mean,
this is it, Brock.

03:56.111 --> 03:57.898
Telepor-freaking-tation.

03:58.029 --> 03:58.988
Can you believe it?

03:58.989 --> 04:01.447
Oh, this is
the kind of game-changer

04:01.575 --> 04:03.316
I've been working for
my entire life.

04:03.452 --> 04:06.945
Yeah, uh, got to make
a quick stop.

04:09.332 --> 04:11.415
Huh, didn't know we had tenants
on this floor.

04:11.543 --> 04:13.580
Or even this floor.

04:13.712 --> 04:15.578
Welcome back, Mr. Samson.

04:15.714 --> 04:17.875
Ohh.
Who's your little friend?

04:18.007 --> 04:19.339
You want to meet her?

04:19.468 --> 04:22.802
Heya, sexy.
A little later. What do you say?

04:22.929 --> 04:24.045
Hmm? Yeah.

04:24.181 --> 04:26.798
Well
Mm...

04:31.146 --> 04:33.809
And now my erection
is completely gone, thank you.

04:33.940 --> 04:35.806
What is all this?

04:35.942 --> 04:39.902
Doc, it's, uh...
Uh, it's time we had the talk.

04:40.030 --> 04:41.692
Now, at 21:00 sharp,

04:41.823 --> 04:43.985
Tunnel V. will move
into position underground,

04:44.117 --> 04:46.655
snug as a bug
next to ol' Doc Venture's lab.

04:46.787 --> 04:48.028
With the subway as cover,

04:48.163 --> 04:49.807
I can tunnel through
the foundation over there,

04:49.831 --> 04:50.892
and no one will
even hear a peep.

04:50.916 --> 04:53.499
At 21:20, I reach
the Ven-Tech ventilation access.

04:53.627 --> 04:55.414
Oh!
That's where I come in!

04:55.545 --> 04:57.753
The vents are laser-shielded
and too small

04:57.881 --> 04:58.962
for any old dum-dum,

04:59.090 --> 05:02.128
so I just presto change-o
into a snake

05:02.260 --> 05:04.297
and slither into the lab.

05:04.429 --> 05:05.886
Presto plugs
this transmitter

05:06.014 --> 05:07.550
into Venture's
security mainframe,

05:07.682 --> 05:10.265
and voilÃ ,
his whole system is my bitch.

05:10.393 --> 05:12.430
Once Dot shuts off the alarms
and opens the doors,

05:12.562 --> 05:14.645
I grab the goods,
load them into Presto.

05:14.773 --> 05:17.891
After I presto change-o
into a human hand truck,

05:18.026 --> 05:20.734
Ooh! A <i>man</i> truck.

05:20.862 --> 05:23.070
We haul them out
the loading dock, south exit.

05:23.198 --> 05:25.406
Where Driver X will be waiting
to whisk y'all

05:25.534 --> 05:27.821
to the safe house
for champagne and revelry.

05:27.953 --> 05:29.069
Questions?

05:29.204 --> 05:30.536
New guy.
How'd I guess?

05:30.664 --> 05:32.584
Yeah, uh, where am I
while all this is happening?

05:32.707 --> 05:35.165
Oh, you're our eyes in the sky,
pretty bird.

05:35.293 --> 05:36.750
Aerial reconnaissance.

05:36.878 --> 05:39.165
You'll be making a big old
loop-de-loop all around

05:39.297 --> 05:40.297
that there Ven-Tech.

05:40.423 --> 05:42.710
- So I'm a lookout?
- Now he gets it.

05:42.843 --> 05:44.425
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa!
Wait a minute!

05:44.553 --> 05:46.761
If anyone should be taking lead
on this thing,

05:46.888 --> 05:47.969
it's the Mighty Monarch.

05:48.098 --> 05:50.841
I've got decades
of hot skinny on Venture.

05:50.976 --> 05:53.184
I know how he thinks,
how he takes his coffee.

05:53.311 --> 05:54.973
I... I can tell you
his Sleep Number!

05:55.105 --> 05:56.892
Sure.
That sounds super useful.

05:57.023 --> 05:59.390
It's 25!
He's soft.

05:59.526 --> 06:02.564
I say we scrap this whole plan
and start from the top.

06:02.696 --> 06:03.777
You don't arch a Venture

06:03.905 --> 06:05.487
by sneaking around
in his crawl space.

06:05.615 --> 06:07.777
You hit him high,
and you hit him hard!

06:07.909 --> 06:09.866
Copycat, you have, like,
a Copy-copter

06:09.995 --> 06:11.702
for the initial aerial assault?

06:11.830 --> 06:14.038
Told you we should've
just bought a drone.

06:14.165 --> 06:15.406
Looky here now, songbird.

06:15.542 --> 06:17.249
I'm the leader
of this here band,

06:17.377 --> 06:19.790
and I say we ain't changing
the set list

06:19.921 --> 06:21.287
an hour before showtime.

06:21.423 --> 06:22.959
An hour before...
Wait. What?!

06:23.091 --> 06:24.172
Oh, yes, sir.

06:24.301 --> 06:29.513
Curtain goes up at 21:00 sharp,
tonightsville.

06:29.639 --> 06:31.596
So you've licked
teleportation, huh?

06:31.725 --> 06:33.466
Well, give yourself
a fat pat on the back.

06:33.602 --> 06:35.343
That's what we
in the supersecret biz

06:35.478 --> 06:36.844
call a game-changer.

06:36.980 --> 06:38.812
Right?
I was just telling Brock...

06:38.940 --> 06:40.647
- That's why you have to kill it.
- What?

06:40.775 --> 06:42.128
Decommission it.
Scrap it for parts.

06:42.152 --> 06:45.486
Torch all your files and never,
ever speak of it again.

06:45.614 --> 06:47.150
Uh, why would I do that?

06:47.282 --> 06:48.989
Okay, let's say
you grace the world

06:49.117 --> 06:51.325
with this technological
brain fart of yours.

06:51.453 --> 06:53.410
Have you given any thought
to what happens next?

06:53.538 --> 06:56.155
Pfft, you mean after
they slap a Nobel on me?

06:56.291 --> 06:59.329
I retire to Spanakopita
on a pile of money and women.

06:59.461 --> 07:01.498
